  "original_title": "\u0daf\u0dd4\u0dbd\u0dcf\u0d82\u0da2\u0dbd\u0dd3 \u0dbb\u0da7\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0dba\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Dulangali leaves the country",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "It is reported that Mrs. Dulangali Jayakodi, the sister of opposition leader Mr. Sajith Premadasa, who was recently recorded by the Criminal Investigation Department regarding the incident of Mr. Ranil Wickramasinghe's personal home in Kollupitiya being destroyed by fire, has left the island yesterday (26) morning.",
        "She has left the island with the two children Sanjay Jayakodi and Amaya Jayakodi on Sri Lankan Airlines flight UL 505.",
        "Ms. Dulangali Jayakodi was summoned to the Criminal Investigation Department and a statement was recorded on the last 20th Saturday regarding the incident of Mr. Ranil Wickramasinghe's personal house in Kollupitiya being destroyed by fire.",
        "Ranil Wickramasinghe's private house in Kollupitiya was set on fire by a group of violent people on 9th July last, and many valuable books and other property were destroyed.",
        "The Criminal Investigation Department recorded a statement from Mrs. Dulanjali Jayagoda based on information that she was present at the time of the incident."
      ],
